ScenePlay schema migrations (Flask-Migrate / Alembic)
=====================================================

How migrations run here
-----------------------
Boxes are appliances — nobody runs `flask db upgrade` on them. Instead app.py
applies pending revisions programmatically at startup:

    sql.create_table()   # raw-SQL tables (CREATE IF NOT EXISTS)
    db.create_all()      # SQLAlchemy-model tables
    flask_migrate.upgrade()   # versioned patches: columns, indexes, seeds, data

A failed migration RAISES and stops the app — by design. A box that won't
start with a clear error beats one silently running on a half-upgraded schema.

restore_replace() also runs this sequence after swapping the database file, so
restoring an old backup brings it current immediately.

Adding a schema change
----------------------
1. New TABLE: add it to sql.create_table() (raw SQL) or as a model (create_all
   picks it up). No revision needed — both creators are idempotent.
2. New COLUMN / index / seed row / data fix on an EXISTING table: write a new
   revision in versions/ (copy the style of 0001_baseline.py):
     - chain it: down_revision = '<current head>'
     - guard each step (check PRAGMA table_info first) so databases that are
       already current pass through cleanly
     - let real failures raise; never swallow them
3. Do NOT use `flask db migrate` (autogenerate). Most tables are raw SQL with
   no SQLAlchemy model, so autogenerate would propose dropping them.

Fresh installs get the full current schema from step 1 creators; upgrade()
then just stamps the revisions as applied.
